animal.description:
The following is the discription the owner wrote when he dropped Hermes off at the shelter.
While at the shelter we find him to be very happy and loves people. He has been use to living in a truck with his owner and seems ok in a kennel but would not do well in a crate.  Too confining. Don't really think  he would need a crate. Hermes does not like cats so small dogs might be iffy.
To adopt Hermes you must live in Jacksonville. Have a vet reference, a fenced yard,   NO EXCEPTIONS



Hermes is a very sweet and playful boy, he loves attention and smuggling. He doesn't bite and hardly ever barks though,, If he feels like he is being ignored, he'll place himself where you can see him and turn his back on you, peeking over his shoulder to make sure you notice.
 He is house trained and is excellent about holding it. The only issues is when taking him out to potty, he needs to be walked near trees and bushes, he just won't go on grass if being walked, he also doles it out slowly, needing several bushes or trees to empty himself out.
; 
; He seems good with other dogs and would probably love having someone to play with.  He might be okay with cats, but he might want to play when they don't want to, ; 
; Though he is mostly Lab, he doesn't seem to like water much, doesn't like getting his baths either, though hell be okay once you start.
; 
; He loved his squeeky pheasant plush toy and loves little mice made for cats, he tosses them in the air and tries to catch them.
 Loves being called Happy Puppy; and ;good boy .
;  
; He is great with a vacuum going in the room, is okay with thunder.

;  ; 
  He seems good with kids too, sort of indifferent really, but not scared or agitated at all.
; 
  He loves having his neck and chest rubbed too.... 

  .

